@EndNode
@Node "TARGET"

This SW has been developed to help you in learning CW. In its design I
have kept in mind only the italian CW test. So you can't find the same
environment you have at the CW test in your country. I'm very sorry about, 
however you can use this SW for the first steps, and then, try to use 
another software, Morse Trainer, from Antonello Biancalana, @{" IK0TOJ " link "IK0TOJ"}. 

@EndNode
@Node "HOW TO USE"
@Next "AUTHOR"

This software is so simple I think instructions aren't necessary.
However this is a little explanation on how R-Morse works.
R-Morse haven't special requirement. It should work on every Amiga,
from the glorious A1000 with 1.1 and 256 K, to the new 5000....
From OS 2.0+ it gives you the classical 3D look. There is only 
a menu with 5 items: 

      @{" Preferences " link "PREFERENCES"}
      @{"    Table    " link "TABLE"}
      @{"    Words    " link "WORDS"}
      @{"    Groups   " link "GROUPS"}
      @{"    Quit     " link "QUIT"}

@EndNode
@Node "PREFERENCES"
@Prev "QUIT"

Select this item if you want change:
a) volume
b) speed
c) tone frequency
You can also save your preferences in a @{" configuration file " link "CONFIGURATION FILE"}, so
the next time you will load R-Morse, you will retrieve them.

@EndNode
@Node "TABLE"

Select this item if you want see (and hear) the CW codes.
Click on a code to hear it. There are no special codes, for the
italian CW test they are no needed.....:-)     

@EndNode
@Node "WORDS"

Select this item if you want translate words in CW. 
Write inside the input box and then click on Words.
Your words will be capitalized, and strange characters will
be deleted.

@EndNode
@Node "GROUPS"

Select this item if you want see the italian CW test.
This will generate 48 group of 5 either characters or numbers.
There aren't strange characters. You can have a 'hidden'
and a 'interactive' generation of groups according to selected
preferences.  

@EndNode
@Node "QUIT"
@Next "PREFERENCES"

I don't know.....

@EndNode
